From df8abd9ba3e80766dc92c876f3035495d636d6a0 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Andre Mauricio Zelak <andre.zelak@windriver.com>
Date: Sun, 24 May 2026 21:58:10 -0300
Subject: [PATCH 05/11] Force one clock source by configuration

When a HA is enabled and one of the clock sources is configured
with priority 254, the best clock source selection algorithm is
disable, and the source will be selected as source regardless
its state.

Test Plan:
PASS In a system configured as PTP T-BC, using HA spec and two
     sources, one of them with HA priority set to 254.

     system ptp-interface-parameter-add phc-iface01 ha_priority=254
        ha_stability_timer=10

     Given both external GMs are up and matching the HA requirements
     When the phc2sys service starts
     Then the following info messages are printed in the log.

     phc2sys[878093.543]: phcinst0 HA automatic source selection is disabled by configuration
     phc2sys[878093.543]: phcinst0 Only interface enp81s0f3 will be used as source clock

     And the source configured with HA priority 254 is selected source.

     When the GM connected to the selected source degrades
     Then the selected source remains the same.

     When the GM connected to the selected source recovers
     Then the selected source remains the same.

     When the GM connected to the other source degrades
     Then the selected source remains the same.

     When the GM connected to the other source reconver
     Then the selected source remains the same.

Signed-off-by: Andre Mauricio Zelak <andre.zelak@windriver.com>
